{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1641b28b-74d5-46bd-b758-d07fbf609325","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" in results with your reason message visible in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f0820bf-e777-42d9-b11d-265603849923","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to invoke any tools or skills.\n\nHere's the information:\n\n- **MSTest**: `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n- **xUnit**: `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]`\n- **NUnit**: `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n- **TUnit**: `[Skip(\"reason\")]`\n\nI can answer this directly without tools.","outputTokens":433,"requestId":"BD0D:319933:1C9B3BB:20414FE:6A07C4BD"},"id":"a361f0aa-b36f-4fc4-98ec-d90dce6b7973","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:13:41.153Z","parentId":"945c04f8-6534-4edc-a1e6-fff000da20a0"}
